{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id56b2237c-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1909"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1909"},"text":"§ 1909.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Policy on hazing","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56b2237d-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1909/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In General","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Subject to the approval of the Commandant, the Superintendent of the Academy shall issue and make available to the public written policies—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id56b2237e-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1909/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" subject to subsection (d), defining hazing;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id56b2237f-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1909/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" designed to prevent hazing; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id56b22380-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1909/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" prescribing dismissal, suspension, or other adequate punishment for violations.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56b22381-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1909/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Effect of Request for Court-martial","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"If a cadet who is charged with violating a policy issued under subsection (a), the penalty for which is or may be dismissal from the Academy, requests in writing a trial by a general court-martial, the cadet may not be dismissed for that offense except under sentence of such a court.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56b22382-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1909/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Limitation","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"A cadet dismissed from the Academy for hazing or bullying may not be reappointed to the Corps of Cadets, and is ineligible for appointment as commissioned ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002027"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002027"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be preceded by “a”."}],"tail":" officer in a regular component of the Coast Guard, until the date that is 2 years after the date of the graduation of the class of the cadet."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id56b22383-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1909/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definition of Hazing","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In developing the policies under subsection (a)(1), the Superintendent shall, to the maximum extent practicable, define the term “hazing” as the unauthorized assumption of authority by a cadet whereby another cadet suffers or is exposed to any cruelty, indignity, humiliation, hardship, or oppression, or the deprivation or abridgement of any right.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id56b22384-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/dG/tLXXII/s7245/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, div. G, title LXXII, § 7245(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/139/1730"},"text":"139 Stat. 1730","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
